            "text": "<p>As farmers whose family has worked this exact soil for over three hundred years, environmental stewardship is not a modern marketing trend; it is a foundational necessity for our survival. Our viticultural practices are rigorously designed to preserve the delicate ecosystem of the Moselle Valley for the generations that will follow us. By minimizing synthetic intervention in the vineyard, promoting natural biodiversity among the vines, and carefully managing the health of our soils, we ensure that the land remains vibrant. This deep respect for the environment translates directly into the purity, intensity, and pristine quality of the wines we produce.</p>",
